{{Signs of death}}
'''Rigor Mortis''' is a condition that affects a [[human]] [[body]] after [[death]]. Rigor mortis causes the [[muscle]]s in the body to become [[rigid]]. It starts to happen three to four hours after death. Twelve hours after death, the muscles have become fully rigid. The condition usually lasts until 36 hours after death. At that time, the muscles start to relax.

